## Context
Spec writer review found three status inconsistencies:

1. pending is in the valid set but never explained in the spec
2. Peer review example shows log "status pending -> addressed"
   but addressed is not in VALID_STATUSES — validator would reject it
3. Same example shows Status: pending in header after the log says
   it was changed — header should reflect current state

Also: Coordination header description says "forge#N" but examples
use "gh#42". The pattern vs. concrete instance distinction is unclear.

## Actions
1. Add brief explanation of each status value in the spec
2. Either add addressed to valid statuses or change the example
   to show Status: closed (simpler — addressed is peer-review jargon)
3. Fix the peer review example: header should show the current state
4. Clarify Coordination format: "forge-prefix#N" with explicit
   examples (gh#, gl#, gt#)

## Exit criteria
- All example headers match current state after logged events
- All status values used in examples are in VALID_STATUSES
- Coordination format is unambiguous
